METHICILLIN-RESISTANT STAPH. AUREUS, DOGS - CANADA (02)
*********************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
See Also
Methicillin-resistant Staph. aureus, dogs - Canada 2000.3064
[1
Date: 2 Aug 2000 15:27:27 -0400
From: Dr. Hani Dick <dickh@vita-tech.com>

We have conclusively identified the two isolates as MRSA not only by
biochemical reactions but also by sending them to the Provincial Health
Laboratory in Toronto, where they were further confirmed by Thermonuclease
test (both isolates were positive) and by PCR were they were positive for
both FEM and the Mec [mecA genes.
--
Dr. Hani Dick
<dickh@vita-tech.com>
[We appreciate the clarification of these issues by Dr. Dick. -Man. Ed. DS
